Hunger Solutions New York
July 1 at 12:28 PM ¬∑

Pandemic-EBT food benefits will be issued automatically to families whose child(ren) received free or reduced-price lunch at school through the federal lunch program. This includes all students who attend a school that provides free meals for all. Each child will receive $420 on a new or existing EBT card that can be used like a bank debit card to purchase food from participating stores. P-EBT benefits are not limited by immigration status and public charge rules do NOT apply.

Learn more: hungersolutionsny.org/pebt

Liberty Central School District‚ÄéWelcome Back Kick Off
August 10, 2018 at 2:17 PM ¬∑

This kick-off happens the day before the first day of classes. It's a time for students to meet their teachers, throw their back-to-school worries out the window and have fun!

Did you know? This is strictly a volunteer-event for teachers. Teachers do not have to attend, but nearly all of our LES teachers volunteer in one way or another.

Our teachers are really wonderful and caring professionals - we hope you come on Sept. 5 and show them some love!

This kick-off happens the day before the first day of classes. It's a time for students to meet their teachers, throw their back-to-school worries out the window and have fun!

Did you know? This is strictly a volunteer-event for teachers. Teachers do not have to attend, but nearly all of our LES teachers volunteer in one way or another.

Our teachers are really wonderful and caring professionals - we hope you come on Sept. 5 and show them some love!

Liberty Central School District
December 5, 2017 at 11:34 AM ¬∑

Today‚Äôs the day! Grab a friend and go vote! Polls will be open from noon to 9 p.m. at the high school gymnasium for voting on a proposed $560,000 facilities project that will repair and restore the baseball and soccer fields located behind Liberty High School.

The cost of the project will be funded fully from Capital Reserve funds. There will be no increase in taxes to local property owners and we will receive approximately 82 percent in building aid back from New York State Education Department.

It‚Äôs up to you whether or not we address the drainage issues at the fields. Thank you for taking the time to vote for Liberty Pride!
